{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"daca4872-a242-4452-a271-93c329c7481d","content":"In .NET MAUI, those three `Application` overrides no longer exist. The equivalent is to use **`Window` lifecycle events**.\n\n**Option 1 — Override methods on a custom `Window`:**\n\n```csharp\npublic class MyWindow : Window\n{\n    public MyWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }\n\n    protected override void OnCreated()   { /* was OnStart */  }\n    protected override void OnStopped()   { /* was OnSleep */  }\n    protected override void OnResumed()   { /* was OnResume */ }\n}\n```\n\nThen in `App.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n    => new MyWindow(new MainPage());\n```\n\n**Option 2 — Subscribe to events inline in `App.cs`:**\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = new Window(new MainPage());\n    window.Created  += (s, e) => { /* OnStart  */ };\n    window.Stopped  += (s, e) => { /* OnSleep  */ };\n    window.Resumed  += (s, e) => { /* OnResume */ };\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Mapping summary:**\n\n| Xamarin.Forms | .NET MAUI Window |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart()` | `Created` / `OnCreated()` |\n| `OnSleep()` | `Stopped` / `OnStopped()` |\n| `OnResume()` | `Resumed` / `OnResumed()` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f5b50fd1-0fac-4ed1-86e8-9e14bd98ed5b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` on the `Application` class.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the equivalent is to use the `Window` lifecycle events or the `ILifecycleBuilder` in `MauiProgram.cs`. Specifically:\n\n- The `Application` class in MAUI still has `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` — but the recommended approach is to use the **Window lifecycle events** or **platform-specific lifecycle events**.\n\n\n- Actually, I need to correct myself — `OnStart`, `OnSleep`, and `OnResume` don't actually exist on the MAUI `Application` class. The MAUI `Application` class is fundamentally different from Xamarin.Forms, so you need to use `CreateWindow()` to override window lifecycle events instead.\n\nThe lifecycle mapping works like this: `Window.Created` or `OnCreated()` replaces `OnStart`, `Window.Stopped` or `OnStopped()` replaces `OnSleep`, and `Window.Resumed` or `OnResumed()` replaces `OnResume`.","outputTokens":983,"requestId":"D441:6467:1D20176:20B8982:6A07C249"},"id":"dd85adbe-8d9d-4ae9-a35f-fb729107b40f","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:03:23.407Z","parentId":"2b205910-326b-45f8-a117-24f2aeaa8217"}
